EFG is one of Temenos's longest-standing clients and was among the very first banks to adopt the T24 platform. In 2016, when EFG acquired BSI (which ran on Avaloq's Banking Suite), the decision was made to migrate the entire BSI business onto T24. This migration completed in 2018 at a cost of CHF 80m.

In 2023, EFG completed a further "successful upgrade of its Core Banking Platform in all banking booking centres globally." This was a major programme — all costs were expensed, and the bank wrote down legacy IT solutions being decommissioned as part of this work.

**Implication for Infosys:** The core banking foundation is Temenos T24, now upgraded. Temenos itself is investing heavily in AI — it announced new AI products (Product Manager Co-Pilot and FCM AI Agent) in 2025, integrated with Microsoft Azure OpenAI. EFG may seek to leverage these native Temenos AI capabilities. Infosys must position its offering as complementary to — not competing with — the Temenos roadmap.

