## 14. Risk Factors for Infosys to Be Aware Of

**The Temenos relationship is protective.** EFG has a deep, decades-long relationship with Temenos. Any Infosys proposal that appears to compete with or undermine the Temenos platform will face internal resistance. The pitch must explicitly position Infosys as building on top of T24, not replacing it.

**Aladdin Wealth is a recent, high-profile commitment.** EFG has just announced the BlackRock Aladdin Wealth integration. Infosys cannot be seen as duplicating what Aladdin Wealth does. The positioning must be complementary — Aladdin Wealth handles the investment intelligence layer; Infosys handles the workflow, data, and operational automation layer beneath it.

**CRO culture will resist change.** Any tool that CROs experience as surveillance, standardisation of their approach, or threat to client ownership will be rejected. Infosys must demonstrate experience building technology that CROs choose to adopt, not technology that is mandated on them.

**FINMA will have opinions about AI vendors.** EFG cannot engage an AI vendor whose data practices are inconsistent with Swiss data sovereignty requirements. Infosys must be prepared to address data residency, audit rights, and exit strategy questions from the compliance function.

**The ROI expectation is 2 years.** EFG's own data shows that BFS AI budgets expect ROI within two years. Infosys must be prepared to commit to measurable outcomes at defined milestones — not multi-year transformation promises.

